               <p>WILLIAM WILSON. I am a <rs id="t18280221-132-viclabel701" type="occupation">plumber</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-132-victim842 t18280221-132-viclabel701"></join>. On the 31st of January the prisoner came to my house, to look at an apartment. I was in my back shop; my servant called me, and the prisoner took an opportunity of going down into the kitchen - the servant told me he had gone out - I ran out, and took him about one hundred, or one hundred and fifty yards off - he gave me these spoons out of his pocket - they are mine.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-132-person843">
                  CECILIA 
                  HANNAH POPE
               <interp inst="t18280221-132-person843" type="surname" value="HANNAH POPE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-132-person843" type="given" value="CECILIA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-132-person843" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in the service of Mr. Wilson. I let the prisoner in, and he asked to look at the first floor, which was to let - I showed it him - I went to call my master - when I came back he was coming up the kitchen stairs; I heard the spoons rattle - the prisoner then<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182802210092"></xptr>went out; I told my master, who pursued him, and brought him back with the spoons.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 68.</p>
